cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with image-based clothing retrieval, which is a computer vision problem, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The use of relevance feedback and Bayesian formulation suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.IR (information retrieval) and cs.LG (machine learning). The use of heterogeneous features extracted from multiple clothing attributes suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.MM (multimedia) and the use of user feedback suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.HC (human-computer interaction).
